'''''Le Jeu de la Mort''''' ''(The Game of Death)'' is a [[France|French]]/[[Switzerland|Swiss]] television [[documentary]] broadcast by the French public television channel [[France 2]]. It was presented as a [[social commentary]] on the effects of obeying orders and humiliation in [[reality television]], and its broadcast was followed by a studio discussion on the programme.<ref name="bbc-jeudelamort">{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/8573755.stm|title=Row over 'torture' on French TV|last=Chazan|first=David|date=March 18, 2010|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=18 March 2010}}</ref>

The documentary focused on a modern version of the [[Milgram experiment]], with the additional factor of reality television's popularity and influence on the general public. The experiment was performed in the guise of a [[game show]] known as ''La Zone Xtrême''. Volunteers were given €40 to take part as contestants in a "[[Television pilot|pilot]]" for the fictitious show, where they had to administer increasingly stronger electric shocks to trained actors posing as players as punishment for incorrect answers, as encouraged to do so by the host and audience.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/35918059/ns/entertainment-television/|title=Fake TV show has players electrocuting others|last=Keaton, Jamey|date=March 17, 2010|accessdate=18 March 2010}}</ref> Only 16 of 80 "contestants" chose to end the game before delivering the highest voltage punishment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=124838091|title=Fake TV Game Show 'Tortures' Man, Shocks France|website=[[npr.org]]|accessdate=2010-10-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.france24.com/en/20100317-disturbing-tv-docu-game-tests-limits-small-screen-power-france-game-of-death |title=Fake torture TV 'game show' reveals willingness to obey |date=2010-03-17 |accessdate=2010-03-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100323051311/http://www.france24.com/en/20100317-disturbing-tv-docu-game-tests-limits-small-screen-power-france-game-of-death |archivedate=2010-03-23 |df= }}</ref>

