{{Infobox sailor |name = Pierre de Boulogne |image = Sidi-Fekkar Fries Scheepvaartmuseum 1910.jpg |image_size = |caption = The yacht Sidi-Fekkar that was crewed by Pierre de Boulogne during the [[Sailing at the 1900 Summer Olympics – .5 to 1 ton|1900 Olympics]] |birth_name = |fullname = |nickname = |nationality = France |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |height = |classes = [[Ton class|0.5 to 1 ton]] |club = |coach = | medaltemplates-title = Competition record | medaltemplates = {{MedalSport|[[Sailing at the Summer Olympics|Sailing]]}} {{Medal|Country|{{FRA}}}} {{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]] [[File:Olympic rings without rims.svg|50px]]}} {{Medal | DQ | [[Sailing at the 1900 Summer Olympics – .5 to 1 ton|1900 Paris]] | [[Ton class|0.5 to 1 ton 1st race]]}} {{Medal | | [[Sailing at the 1900 Summer Olympics – .5 to 1 ton|1900 Paris]] | [[Ton class|0.5 to 1 ton 2nd race]] (DNF)}} | show-medals = yes | updated = 8 May 2015 }}
'''Pierre de Boulogne''' was a [[sailor]] from [[France]],<ref name="A" /> who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1900 Summer Olympics – .5 to 1 ton|1900 Summer Olympics]] in [[Meulan]], [[France]]. Pierre de Boulogne as crew, was disqualified in first race of the [[Ton class|0.5 to 1 ton]] and did not finished in the second race. He did this with the boat ''Sidi-Fekkar''.
